query.result:
10 Cursed are you, ancient she-wolf, 11 who more than all other beasts have preyed 12 for your endless, gloomy hunger!
13 O heaven, in whose revolving it seems one believes 14 the conditions of here below to be transmuted, 15 when will come he for whom this departs?
16 We went with slow and scarce steps, 17 and I attentive to the shadows, which I felt 18 pitiably weeping and lamenting;
19 and by chance I heard “Sweet Mary!” 20 before us called thus in the weeping 21 as does a woman who is in labor;
22 and following: “Poor you were so much, 23 as can be seen for that hospice 24 where you unburdened your holy burden.”

